Key difference:

Feature	                        config-repo/application.yml	                    resources/application.yml
Where it lives	                GitHub / external repo	                        Inside the app
Source of truth	                Yes, central	                                No, fallback
Can change without rebuild	    Yes	                                            No
Used for Spring Cloud Config	Yes	                                            No
Local dev fallback	            Optional	                                    Yes

Rule of thumb:
Use config-repo for all shared/production config.
Keep resources/application.yml minimal — mostly for local defaults or dev profiles.